<H1>Using 3M 467MP adhesive to reapply pinball stickers</H1>
<P><A href="mailto:billg4me@yahoo.com">billg4me@yahoo.com</A></P>
<HR>

<br>

Stickers are often used on the underside of clear plastic pinball ramps.&nbsp;
They usually contain some sort of artwork or game play directions.&nbsp; There
are times when they need to be reapplied.&nbsp; This includes:
<ul>
  <li>Installation of a NOS ramp and the need to transfer existing stickers to
    the new ramp</li>
  <li>Stickers that have lost their adhesive and no longer stick to the ramp</li>
</ul>
<p>This web page is put together to share the information and tips I gathered while
using 3M 467MP adhesive to reapply a ramp sticker.&nbsp; Click on pictures for
their full image.</p>
<UL>
  <LI><A href="#467MP">467MP adhesive</A> 
  <LI><A href="#apply_adhesive">Applying adhesive</A> 
  <LI><A href="#install">Installation of new sticker</A> 
</UL>


<HR>
<H1><A name=467MP>3M 467MP Adhesive</A></H1>
<table border="4" width="95%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
  <tr>
    <td width="100%">
      <table border="1" width="100%" cellpadding="10" cellspacing="0">
        <tr>
          <td width="50%" valign="top" align="left">3M's 467MP Adhesive is a product that I learned about&nbsp; through
      the&nbsp; <a href="http://groups.google.com/groups?num=25&amp;hl=en&amp;lr=&amp;group=rec.games.pinball&amp;safe=off&amp;start=0&amp;group=rec.games.pinball">rec.games.pinball</a>
      newsgroup.&nbsp; It comes off the roll like double sided tape, but with no
      tape - just adhesive.&nbsp; I used it to reapply the ramp sticker on my
      Williams Comet.
      <p>To remove a ramp sticker I highly recommend using Goo Gone to dissolve
      the existing sticker adhesive.&nbsp; I like to use an artist brush with
      stiff nylon bristles to gently work the Goo Gone between the ramp and
      sticker.&nbsp; Take your time and don't get impatient.&nbsp; I probably
      spent 15-20 minutes removing the sticker in the picture.</p>
      <p>Bob Ellingson has posted in <a href="http://groups.google.com/groups?num=25&amp;hl=en&amp;lr=&amp;group=rec.games.pinball&amp;safe=off&amp;start=0&amp;group=rec.games.pinball">rec.games.pinball</a>
      that he's ordered a case of the 467MP adhesive to sell to rgp'ers.&nbsp;&nbsp;
      Contact him via email at <a href="mailto:sss@sss">bobe@halted.com</a> for pricing
      information.</p>
          </td>
          <td width="25%" valign="top" align="center">
