<H1><A name=apply_adhesive>Applying Adhesive</A></H1>
<table border="4" width="95%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
  <tr>
    <td width="100%">
      <table border="1" width="100%" cellpadding="10" cellspacing="0">
        <tr>
          <td width="50%" valign="top" align="left"><P>
      Before applying the adhesive to the sticker make sure it's nice and clean
      and free of any old adhesive.&nbsp; I just used additional Goo Gone and made a final cleaning
      with Windex.</P><P>Roll out the adhesive the length needed and place it's
      paper side down on a hard smooth surface.&nbsp; Next, lightly mist the TOP
      side of the sticker with Windex and lay it on the sticky adhesive that's
      facing up.&nbsp; The Windex helps allow time to move the sticker in
      place and smooth out any wrinkles.&nbsp; Slowly keep squeegeeing the
      Windex out between the adhesive and the sticker.&nbsp; In about 5 minutes
      the adhesive will take hold.&nbsp; Set aside for an hour.</P><P>&nbsp;</P></td>
          <td width="25%" valign="top" align="center"><A 
      href="stickem.jpg"><IMG 
      height=200 src="stickem_t.jpg" width=200 
border=1></A>
      <p align="center"><A 
      href="stickem.jpg">Apply adhesive to sticker backing</A></p>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td width="50%" valign="top" align="left">
      I liked to remove the excessive adhesive by gently rolling it away from
      the sticker.&nbsp; I did this to give a nice clean adhesive edge to the
      sticker.&nbsp; This way when the sticker is unpealed the adhesive won't
      try to pull away from the edge.&nbsp;</td>
          <td width="25%" valign="top" align="center"><a href="excessstickem.jpg"><IMG src="excessstickem_t.jpg" 
      border=0 width="200" height="200"></a>
            <p><a href="excessstickem.jpg">Roll off excess adhesive
      </a></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td width="50%" valign="top" align="left">After all the excessive adhesive was removed, I set the sticker aside
      for 12 hours.&nbsp; I'll be the first to admit that this is probably
      overkill, but I wanted to allow time for the adhesive to cure and really
      bond to the sticker backing.</td>
          <td width="25%" valign="top" align="center"><a href="nostickem.jpg"><IMG 
      height=200 src="nostickem_t.jpg" width=200 
      border=0></a>
      <p align="center"><a href="nostickem.jpg">Excess adhesive removed</a></td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>
<P><a href="#top">Top</a><br>
</P>
<h1><A name=install>Installation of new sticker</A></h1>
<table border="4" width="95%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
  <tr>
    <td width="100%">
      <table border="1" width="100%" cellpadding="10" cellspacing="0">
        <tr>
          <td width="50%" valign="top" align="left">Just like the sticker, make
      sure the ramp is nice and clean and free of any old adhesive.&nbsp; I just used additional Goo Gone and made a final cleaning
      with Windex.</td>
          <td width="25%" valign="top" align="center"><a href="nakedramp.jpg"><IMG 
      height=200 src="nakedramp_t.jpg" width=200 
      border=0></a><BR><a href="nakedramp.jpg"><br>
            Ramp ready for sticker</a> 
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td width="50%" valign="top" align="left">
      Before pealing off the sticker, I lightly mist the back side of the
      plastic ramp with Windex.&nbsp; This helps allow time to move the
      sticker in place and smooth out any wrinkles.&nbsp; Much like applying the
      adhesive,&nbsp; slowly keep squeegeeing the
      Windex out between the sticker and the ramp.&nbsp; In about 5 minutes
      the adhesive will take hold.&nbsp; Here's a finished look from the
      backside of the ramp.</td>
          <td width="25%" valign="top" align="center"> 
      <P><a href="backdone.jpg"><IMG 
      height=200 src="backdone_t.jpg" width=200 
      border=0></a><BR><a href="backdone.jpg"><br>
      New sticker - back view</a></P>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td width="50%" valign="top" align="left">
      <p>Here's a look from the top of the ramp.&nbsp; The picture glare doesn't
      help, but the sticker is clean and crisp with no signs of the adhesive.</p>
      <p>That's about it.&nbsp; One thing I did before using the adhesive on the
      actual sticker was play around with other sticker like materials.&nbsp; I
      ended up using a candy bar wrapper - Snickers for me :-).</p>
            &nbsp;</td>
          <td width="25%" valign="top" align="center"><a href="topdone.jpg"><IMG 
      height=200 src="topdone_t.jpg" width=200 
      border=0></a><BR><a href="topdone.jpg"><br>
            New sticker - top view</a> 
          </td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>
